                     <interp inst="def1-1242-18400406" type="given" value="WILLIAM"></interp>
                     <hi rend="largeCaps">WILLIAM SHERMAN</hi>
                  </persName> was indicted<rs id="t18400406-1242-offence-1" type="offenceDescription">
                     <interp inst="t18400406-1242-offence-1" type="offenceCategory" value="theft"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18400406-1242-offence-1" type="offenceSubcategory" value="simpleLarceny"></interp> for stealing, on the <rs id="t18400406-cd-200" type="crimeDate">
                        <join result="offenceCrimeDate" targOrder="Y" targets="t18400406-1242-offence-1 t18400406-cd-200"></join>16th of January</rs>, 11 writing-desks, value 4<hi rend="italic">l</hi>. 10<hi rend="italic">s</hi>. 8<hi rend="italic">s</hi>., the goods of <persName id="t18400406-name-1237" type="victimName">
                        <interp inst="t18400406-name-1237" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18400406-name-1237" type="surname" value="BURGESS"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18400406-name-1237" type="given" value="GEORGE HENRY"></interp>
                        <join result="offenceVictim" targOrder="Y" targets="t18400406-1242-offence-1 t18400406-name-1237"></join>George Henry Burgess</persName>.</rs>
               </p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18400406-name-1238" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18400406-name-1238" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18400406-name-1238" type="surname" value="BURGESS"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18400406-name-1238" type="given" value="GEORGE HENRY"></interp>GEORGE HENRY BURGESS</persName>
                  </hi>. I am a cabinet-maker, and live in Bath-street, Leonard-square. On the 16th of January the prisoner applied to me for twelve writing-desks—I had but eleven—he said they would do—he asked me to sell them to him—I asked if he could pay for them—he said, "No"</p>
               <xptr type="pageFacsimile" doc="184004060184"></xptr>
               <p>—he asked if I had a servant that could go with him to a customer he had got for them—I said I would allow my servant to take them to the house, and bring the money to me, and his profit was to be allowed out of the money—my servant went, and came home drunk without the money or the desks—they have not been found.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18400406-name-1239" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18400406-name-1239" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18400406-name-1239" type="surname" value="ATKINS"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18400406-name-1239" type="given" value="JAMES"></interp>JAMES ATKINS</persName>
                  </hi>. I went with the desks—I was to carry them to the place the prisoner had to sell them to, and receive 4<hi rend="italic">l</hi>. 10<hi rend="italic">s</hi>. 8<hi rend="italic">d</hi>. for the eleven desks—we went from shop to shop and did not sell one, till it came rather late in the evening, and having many pots of beer, which he paid for, I got a little too much, and all I can recollect at last was, we went to a house to leave the desks, he took me to a lodging-house to sleep, and said he would take me to some more shops to sell them—he then said he was going backwards—he did not pay the money for the lodging—the landlady said so—I went next day, and could get no intelli<lb></lb>gence of the desks—I carried part of them to the house—they were too heavy for one to carry—I never received the money.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18400406-name-1240" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18400406-name-1240" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18400406-name-1240" type="surname" value="HAMILTON"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18400406-name-1240" type="given" value="HENRY"></interp>HENRY HAMILTON</persName>
                  </hi>. I am shopman to Charles Daniels. About ten o'clock at night, on the 16th of January, the prisoner came with Atkins, and offered some desks for sale—we said we did not want any—he asked to leave them till morning—I said I did not mind, and in the morning the prisoner came by himself and took them away.</p>
               <p>
